#   JS-014 [cleanup]: adopt a least-surprising C++ style (Google C++) + prune dead surface

`js/` is deliberately C++ (JSC); ratify ONE external standard, add a checked-in
`.clang-format`, converge naming, and prune the dead/unused surface. User-requested
cleanup. Method: [Issues].

##  Input

### Context
 -  Naming is mixed: `JS*` / `io_*` / `mmap_free` / `timeout_cb` snake-case vs
    `JABCutf8b…`. No checked-in `.clang-format`; file/TU org is ad hoc.
 -  Dead/unused surface: `JABC_FN_ARG_ALLOC_STRING` (uninitialised-pointer "loaded
    gun", unused), `JABC_FN_ARG_STRING` (raw VLA), the unused
    `JS_SET_PROPERTY_RO`/`JS_GET_PROPERTY`/`JS_TO_NUMBER`/`JS_ADD_METHOD`/
    `JABC_FN_CALL` macros, the declared-but-undefined `JABCutf8cpMakeValueRef` /
    `JABCutf8bFeedStringRef`, the no-op `JABsane` empty-`if` assert
    (`utf8.cpp:50-61`), the dead `convert.cpp`/rdx chain (gate or remove), and the
    trace `printf`/`fprintf(stderr,…)` left in (`main.cpp:129/142`, `io.cpp:282/325/
    341` — violates CLAUDE.md §11).
 -  `WITH_JS`-gated WIP. This ticket is STYLE + dead-code only.

### Goals
 -  One ratified external C++ standard (proposed: Google C++), a checked-in
    `.clang-format`, converged naming, and the dead surface pruned/gated.

### Constraints
 -  ABC slice / `ok64` discipline STAYS at the C-data boundary (that's JS-002..005,
    NOT this ticket). Ratify the exact standard in this ticket before reformatting.

